title: Ansel Adams Photographs
description: This online collection consists of digitized images selected from the Library's 485 black and white, silver gelatin prints by Ansel Adams. Adams took the photographs between 1962 and 1968\; they document the land, building sites, and early activities of the University of California Santa Cruz campus.
rightsStatement: Copyright for this work resides with the Regents of the University of California. The digital copy of this work is intended to support research, teaching, and private study. The publication or use of any work protected by copyright beyond that allowed by fair use for research or educational purposes requires written permission from the copyright owner. For permission to publish or to reproduce the material, or to order an image, please contact the California Museum of Photography at UC Riverside.
rightsHolder: Regents of the University of California
publisher: University of California, Santa Cruz. McHenry Library, Special Collections. 1156 High Street. Santa Cruz, CA, 95064. (831) 459-2547. speccoll@library.ucsc.edu

title: UC Santa Cruz: first registration day
creator: http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n79056359
staffNote: Chancellor's Memo, July 1965: "Over 600 students will begin orientation and registration on Tuesday and Wednesday, September 28-29 with sixty members of the faculty on hand to welcome and counsel. Instruction will start on Monday, October 4. Of the initial student group, 500 will be freshmen, most of the remainder juniors, but a half dozen will be graduate students. Over 500 students have requested University housing in the fall, causing the Business Services and Physical Planning offices to make arrangements for two additional clusters of trailers with total accommodations for 512 students."  This image is duplicated in ms0002_pho_0046, ms0002_pho_0047, ms0002_pho_0061, ms0002_pho_0062, ms0002_pho_0063, and ms0002_pho_0380.
